text:
Tried the Roasted Duck Noodles ($4.50) and Char Siew Roast Pork Rice ($4.50). Comes with soup. Reasonable prices.

Both dishes taste not bad. Meats were nice, not tough, and the sauce tasty. Roast pork skin crunchy. Good option for roast meats if you're in the area.

$4.50 for roasted pork noodle. Value for money.
It was ok ok..
The coffee shop is nice. Quite cooling during lunch time.
Good roast pork and char siew.  Malaysian style noodles.  Another good option of roasted meat stalls in Bedok. Recommended üëçüèº

The better shop in the same block closed due to CNY. Had no choice but to order from here. The Worker here Very very bad attitude. Taunted and replying in a very rude manner in every question we asked . We are there to give him business not see his black face and bad attitude. I will give it a miss at all cost. Food is so so only.

Ordered the steamed chicken rice @ $3.50. Reasonable prices, fragrant rice and juicy chicken breast slices. The soup is also very tasty.

The chilli is not your typical chicken rice chilli. It is more of a garlic chili which does not really match with the chicken rice.
